lenders.name: Shica ♥
lenders.loan_because: everyone deserves a chance.
lenders.occupational_info:
I'm just you're regular highschooler with a part-time job. 

I work as an After School Program teacher with an incorporation called Center for Pan Asian Community Services! I tutor math and reading, teach piano and fundamentals of music, and participate in activities with elementary students. 

As a teenager, the money that I put into Kiva might be the money I would normally spend on a new shirt, trendy jeans, a purse, or a quick meal and movie with some friends. 

But knowing my $25 dollars will become so much more for a hard-working single parent with a much-lower-than-minimum wage, or a large family in dire situation, or a teacher, or a baker, or a farmer, or a whatever it is that allows somewhat of an income...the people who go through more hardships each DAY than I have in my entire upper-middle class suburban LIFE?

That means more than the world to me, infinitely more than what $25 can buy. 

I truly hope that the small contribution helps each person, group, or family reach each of his/her/their goals in life..
and that each individual finds peace along their pursuit of happiness ♥
